qas.question: How long does the sponsor remain?

answers.text: Sponsorship deals run for four years
Emirates airline is the sponsor from 2015 to 2018

qas.question: What is the competition called now?

context: <a0_0>Since the start of the 1994–95 season, the FA Cup has been sponsored.<a0_0/> However, to protect the identity of the competition, the sponsored name has always included '<b6_0>The FA Cup<b6_0/>' in addition to the sponsor's name, unlike sponsorship deals for the League Cup where the word 'cup' is preceded by only the sponsor's name. <a1_0>Sponsorship deals run for four years<a1_0/>, though – as in the case of E.ON – <a2_0>one-year extensions may be agreed<a2_0/>. <a3_0><b5_0><b9_0>Emirates airline<b9_0/><b5_0/> is the sponsor from 2015 to 2018<a3_0/>, renaming the competition as '<a4_0>The Emirates FA Cup<a4_0/>', unlike previous editions, which included 'The FA Cup in association with <b8_0>E.ON<b8_0/>' and 'The FA Cup with <b7_0>Budweiser<b7_0/>'.
